The principle is probably irony in some cases, but in the case of the Furies it appears to be euphemism. Sometimes we have neither; <I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/De_curiositate*.html#ref65
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Plutarch, <I>De Curios.</I> 12</A>, who says that some of the Greeks call night <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">εὐφρόνη</SPAN> ("kindly"), because it brings good and salutary resolves; others, because it invites gaiety or refreshes the body.


