<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note126" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref126
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">126</A>
According to
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Pliny_the_Elder/4*.html#79
	"TARGET="Pliny"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Pliny,WIDTH,205)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Pliny, <I>N. H.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">IV</SPAN>.79</A>, the Danube rises <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">in Germania iugus montis Abnobae ex adverso Rauraci Galliae oppidi</SPAN>. For the seven months, <I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/valeriusflaccus8.html
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(EClickHere+'Book 8<BR>of the Argonautica'+Lat2+LatSearch+'septem exit</SPAN>',WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Val. Flacc. <SPAN CLASS="small">VIII</SPAN>.186</A>, <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">septem exit aquis, septem ostia pandit</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note127" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref127
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">127</A>
The earlier writers counted only five; Pliny and Ptolemy, six; Strabo, seven.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note128" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref128
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">128</A>
The name of the mouth itself is <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">ἱερόν (στόμα)</SPAN>. <SPAN CLASS="translit_Greek">Stoma</SPAN> (<SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">στόμα</SPAN>) in each of the following names is the word meaning "mouth." <SPAN CLASS="translit_Greek">Naracu</SPAN> cannot be interpreted; those that follow are "beautiful," "false," "north" and "narrow."


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note129" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref129
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
