E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref150
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">150</A>
According to Diod. Sic.
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/3D*.html#59.8
	"TARGET="Diodorus_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Diodorus,WIDTH,185)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(<SPAN CLASS="small">III</SPAN>.59.8)</A>, he was the first to build a splendid temple to Cybele at Pessinus.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note151" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref151
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">151</A>
Modern Angora.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note152" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref152
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">152</A>
The position of <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">curialis</SPAN>, or local senator, was an honorary office, without pay, and imposing many obligations. Therefore many sought to avoid such positions,


<A ID="p247x"></A>and it was necessary to force men to take them. Julian was not always indulgent in such cases; see
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#9.12
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
9.12, below</A>, and <I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/25*.html#4.21
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();"><SPAN CLASS="small">XXV</SPAN>.4.21</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note153" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref153
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">153</A>
Cassius, city praetor in 111 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, was feared as a judge;
	<A HREF="
