That is, of Julian for Constantius.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note182" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref182
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">182</A>
When Hercules entered the country of the Pygmies an army of them attacked him in his sleep, but he gathered them up and packed them in his lion skin.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note183" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref183
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">183</A>
According to Apollodorus
	<A HREF="
https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Apollod.+2.5.11
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(<SPAN CLASS="small">II</SPAN>.5.11)</A> Thiodamas was a neatherd of the Dryopians. Hercules killed and ate one of his cattle, without being disturbed by the scolding of Thiodamas.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note184" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref184
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
