According to Sozomenus, <I>Church History</I>, <SPAN CLASS="small">V</SPAN>.19<!--</A>SOZOMEN5-->, he threw a laurel leaf into the spring, and, when he took it out, found on it a note, which confirmed his hopes.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note189" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref189
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">189</A>
Caesar Gallus, in order to purify the place from pagan


<A ID="p269x"></A> superstition, had caused the remains of martyrs to be brought there.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note190" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref190
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
