Solinus, 32.25</A>,


<A ID="p289x"></A>agrees with Ammianus, and in <A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/solinus3.html#XXXIII
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(EClickHere+'Solinus\' Mirabilia'+Lat2+LatSearch+'delphines</SPAN>',WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">32.26</A>, tells of the destruction of crocodiles by dolphins with sharp dorsal fins.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note231" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref231
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">231</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
