	"TARGET="Herodotus_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Herodotus,WIDTH,220)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="small">II</SPAN>.124.″w


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note240" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref240
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">240</A>
This, of course, is true only when the sun stands directly over their tops.

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
	<P CLASS="b0 a0">
Thayer's Note: — which in turn is not possible at the latitude of Gizeh; as Ammian himself implicitly acknowledges in § 31.
	</DIV>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note241" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Ammian/22*.html#ref241
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
